    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Standardized ideogrammatic symbols used to represent concepts, emotional states, or other information wordlessly and succinctly in electronic communications such as text messages, e-mail, and social media. Originally Japanese, from e: “picture, drawing” and moji “letter, character.”</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
